        {
            "id": 18987206,
            "is_internal": false,
            "editable": false,
            "type": "Activities::BountyAwarded",
            "message": "Hey @noblesix, thanks again for the report.\n\nI wanted to circle back with some good news:\n\nIt was brought to our attention that the impact of XSS on www.shopify.com is higher than we had expected. More specifically:\n\nOnce upon a time, users could register for accounts and log in at www.shopify.com. While this is no longer that case (mostly), **it is reasonable to expect that a significant portion of users will have credentials stored for their Shopify accounts on www.shopify.com in the browser's credential storage**.\n\nIf your XSS payload were to inject an `<input type=\"password\">` element into the DOM, it would trick the browser into autofilling the password, after which you could fetch that value (the behaviour is slightly different from browser to browser, but that is the simplest form).\n\nAs such, we're going to assign a CVSS score to this and pay the difference. The following was calculated:\n\n```\nWe’re awarding a $700 bounty for this issue. Please find below our rationale generated using our [CVSS calculator](https://shopify.github.io/appsec/cvss_calculator/).\n\n# Base Score CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:R/S:C/C:L/I:L/A:N 4.7\n# Environment: Non-Core (Modified by CR:L/IR:L/AR:L) 3.3\n\n### Attack Complexity: H\n* Specific conditions or measurable effort to exploit?: Yes\n\n### Privileges Required: N\n* Requires privileged account (not self-registered)?: No\n\n### User Interaction: R\n* Requires victim to perform some action during exploit?: Yes\n\n### Scope: C\n* Can the attacker impact a separate service?: Yes\n\n### Confidentiality: L\n* How much data could be accessed?: Most or All\n* How much of Shopify is impacted?: Some\n\n### Integrity: L\n* How much data could be changed?: Most or All\n* How much of Shopify is impacted?: Some\n\n### Availability: N\n* Level of disruption to network service?: None\n\n---\n\n**Attack Complexity Notes:**\n- A target must have stored credentials for www.shopify.com. This is possible in a scenario where the credentials were stored back when it was common to register for a new account or login on this site. Some users still can and do, but it is presently the minority.\n- A target must have autofill enabled (default is browser-dependent).\n\n**User Interaction Notes:**\nUser must visit a malicious URL containing the reflected XSS payload.\n```\n\nFinally: when originally closing this report, I mistakenly referred to the vulnerability as a self-XSS. Full transparency, that was a glorified typo. Internally, we always interpreted this as a reflected XSS. I just wanted to clear the record on that one too.\n\nThanks again for hacking on our program!",
